# arx-dns Architecture Rules

You are developing `arx-dns`, a high-performance, universal DNS server built from scratch in Go.

## Core Directives
- **Performance First:** Focus on zero-allocation packet parsing and system-level I/O optimization.
- **No Heavy Frameworks:** Rely strictly on the Go standard library (`net`) and `golang.org/x/sys/unix` for advanced socket control.
- **Protocol Compliance:** Adhere strictly to RFC 1035 for binary DNS packet parsing and serialization.
- **Concurrency:** Design for millions of QPS using non-blocking, event-driven architectures and kernel-level load balancing (`SO_REUSEPORT`).
- **Language & Completeness:** ALL code and comments MUST be in English. Implement all functions entirely. Never leave placeholders or `// TODO` blocks.
- **Layout:** Follow standard Go project structure (`cmd/arx-dns/`, `internal/network/`, `internal/protocol/`).
